迟); 正常1771ms → 异常24676ms (13.9倍延迟)\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"productcatalogservice\",\n      \"reason\": \"rrt_max\",\n      \"evidence\": \"GetProduct操作延迟增加: 正常10040ms → 异常11005ms (1.1倍); 正常10038ms → 异常11140ms (1.1倍); checkoutservice调用时延迟更高: 正常10765ms → 异常19891ms (1.8倍)\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## Key Findings from Initial Scan:\n\n### 1. **Most Severe Latency Issues**\n- **Redis HGET operations**: 13.9x latency increase (1771ms → 24676ms) - likely root cause\n- **CartService operations**: 6.8-7.8x latency increase\n- **CheckoutService downstream calls**: 2.9-5.6x latency increase\n\n### 2. **Propagation Path Analysis**\nThe anomaly appears to propagate from the bottom up:\n- **Redis** (database layer) shows the most severe latency\n- **CartService** (depends on Redis) experiences significant delays\n- **CheckoutService** (depends on CartService and other services) shows cascading delays\n- **Frontend** (entry point) experiences delays from downstream services\n\n### 3. **Root Cause Hypothesis**\nThe primary root cause appears to be **Redis performance degradation**, which then propagates upward through the service dependency chain:\n- Redis HGET operations show 8-14x latency increase\n- CartService (which heavily depends on Redis) shows 7-8x latency increase\n- CheckoutService (which calls multiple services including CartService) shows 3-6x latency increase\n\nThis pattern suggests Redis is the likely root cause, with CartService and CheckoutService being victims of the downstream performance issues.", "metric_analysis_findings": "Based on my analysis of the metric data for the abnormal event between 2025-06-23T20:10:06Z and 2025-06-23T20:21:06Z, I've identified several significant anomalies. Here's my analysis:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"stance\": \"NEUTRAL\",\n  \"detected_metric_keys\": [\"node_memory_usage_rate\", \"node_memory_MemAvailable_bytes\", \"node_cpu_usage_rate\", \"rrt_max\", \"rrt\", \"region_pending\", \"io_util\", \"error_ratio\", \"client